  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Risk-based Child Labour Monitoring and Remediation System in Cameroon (RB CLMRS CMR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will contribute to identify, prevent and address child labour in Cargill&#x2019;s cocoa supply chain in Cameroon. To achieve this, Cargill, Telcar and ICI are working together to establish a risk-based Child Labour Monitoring and Remediation System (CLMRS). The proposed CLMRS will allow a more efficient and faster identification of child labour incidents, assign the necessary remediation activities, and prevent future cases by addressing the root causes. The project will reach more than 50,000 producers and their families in Cargill-Telcar&#x2019;s cocoa supply chain in Cameroon living in 1,146 communities.The project will include the following interventions:&#x2022; Risk-based CLMRS: monitoring system based on predefined risk factors in Cargill&#x2019;s cocoa supply chain to identify child labour cases through data collection and raise awareness at household, farm and community levels.&#x2022; Targeted remediation for child labour cases: remediation activities to identified child labour cases at household and community levels.&#x2022; Prevention through increased income: income generating activities for women and youth will be supported to increase the income of cocoa households and therefore prevent child labour.The knowledge, lessons learned and good practices accumulated from the project will provide valuable information on child labour in the cocoa supply chain in Cameroon. This body of knowledge will provide guidance on sustainable models for the elimination and prevention of child labour in the cocoa sector as well as in other supply chains.</narrative>
  </description>
